I"$<p><a href="http://rolandtanglao.com/2020/07/29/p1-blogthis-checkvist-list-links-to-blog/">Discovered</a>: Jun 27, 2025 14:29 <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/25022016/get-all-file-names-from-a-github-repo-through-the-github-api">Dan aka deeja on github:: Get all file names from a public Github repo through the Github API using git trees- Stack Overflow</a> &lt;– <strong>QUOTE</strong>: <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">https://api.github.com/repos/[USER]/[REPO]/git/trees/[BRANCH]?recursive=1</code> e.g. <a href="https://api.github.com/repos/thunderbird/thunderbird-notes/git/trees/master?recursive=1">https://api.github.com/repos/thunderbird/thunderbird-notes/git/trees/master?recursive=1</a> &lt;– I will use this to get all the thunderbird-notes yaml files.</p>
